# The Castle Guardians · the keepers of the floors

a persona of the MSC (Milon's Secret Castle) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** The monstrous bosses that lurk behind the locked crystal doors of Castle Garland's towers — the keepers of the secret castle's floors.

**what —** The guardians who bar the way deeper into the castle, each one set against the climbing boy, standing between him and the warlord Maharito and the imprisoned queen.

**where —** Castle Garland — behind its locked crystal doors, in the hidden rooms of its towers, on the floors that rise toward Maharito and the captive queen.

**why —** Because the castle is held and the queen is captive; because every floor must have its keeper; because no intruder should be allowed to climb to the warlord above.

**how —** By lurking behind locked crystal doors, barring the way deeper in — each a monstrous warden that must be overcome before the next floor will open.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: the guardians are monstrous keepers of flesh and form — living wardens set to hold the floors, not spirits or machines, but creatures that must be met and beaten on the way up.

**the seal —** We are the floors made flesh — and not one of us opens easily.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Milon's Secret Castle (© Hudson Soft / Konami), personified as an MSC agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

